<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910628-0152</DOCNO><DOCID>910628-0152.</DOCID><HL>   Advanced Magnetics   And M.L. Technology   Sign Preliminary Pact</HL><DATE>06/28/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4C</SO><CO>   ADMG</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY, GENETIC RESEARCH, PROSTHETICS (MTC)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Advanced Magnetics Inc. said it signeda preliminary agreement to buy a common-stock purchasewarrant and certain technology rights from M.L. TechnologyVentures L.P., for $10.8 million.   Under the agreement, Advanced Magnetics will buy a warrantto purchase 380,000 shares of Advanced Magnetics commonstock, which is now owned by M.L. Technology, at $10.50 ashare, the company said. Advanced Magnetics also willpurchase &quot;all present and future rights&quot; of M.L. Technologyin a joint venture it formed last year with AdvancedMagnetics.</LP><TEXT>   M.L. Technology is a research and development partnershipmanaged by the Sprout Group, an affiliate of Donaldson,Lufkin andamp; Jenrette Securities Corp. The joint venture itformed with Advanced Magnetics is developing &quot;contrastagents&quot; to enhance images of internal organs made withmagnetic resonance imaging machines.   Advanced Magnetics said it will purchase the warrant andtechnology rights from M.L. Technology with $1.6 million cashand $9.2 million of Advanced Magnetics common stock. Between375,000 and 460,000 Advanced Magnetics common shares will beused to make the purchase, Advanced Magnetics added. Thecompany now has about 3.4 million common shares outstanding.   Completion of the transaction is subject to a definitiveagreement and other conditions, the company said.   For the second quarter ended March 31, Advanced Magneticsearned $2.1 million, or 57 cents a share, on revenue of $5.9million.</TEXT></DOC>